1. **Calculate 30% of 1400 grams:**
   \[
   30\% \text{ of } 1400 = 0.3 \times 1400 = 420 \text{ grams}
   \]

2. **Calculate 60% of the result from step 1:**
   \[
   60\% \text{ of } 420 = 0.6 \times 420 = 252 \text{ grams}
   \]

Alternatively, we can compute it in a single step by multiplying the percentages first:
\[
60\% \times 30\% = 0.6 \times 0.3 = 0.18
\]
Then,
\[
0.18 \times 1400 = 252 \text{ grams}
\]

Both methods confirm that the result is **252 grams**, which corresponds to option **C**.

Answer: C
